I first saw the little periscope mirror one night when Lauren was over.  We were in the bedroom and everything was going great, you know, when all of a sudden she let out this little yelp and pointed at this oblong disc just sort of floating in the top right corner of my bedroom.  In it we could see a pair of small dark eyes watching us excitedly.  At first it looked like a hole straight through my wall into someone else\'92s apartment, but when I jumped up to inspect it, the eyes became scared and the person they were attached to turned and began to run away.  In their absence we could see a beach somewhere, the sun beginning to set, which was weird since we live in Ohio and it was like 2:30 in the afternoon.  Lauren was not having it after that and was starting to get dressed, but I was just looking at this thing that kind of hovered wherever I moved it.\
	\'93Here here wait,\'94 I said, and threw my shirt over the top of it.  It looked like a ghost, wearing my Browns jersey.  I\'92m real slick with situations like this so I just hollered at the mirror thing for a while, alot of \'91you better get the fuck away and leave us alone\'92 and showed her that you couldn\'92t see through the shirt or anything.  \
	Things were just getting going again when Lauren let out another scream - the disc, wearing the Browns jersey and everything, was moving around, bumping into shit and knocking pictures off my wall.  I pulled the jersey off and there were like four kids in swimsuits all huddled around looking in.\
	\'93You fucking kids get out of here!\'94 I yelled, shaking the floating mirror thing, and most of them ran away.  There were still a couple of boys down at the bottom of the frame, ducked down like I couldn\'92t see them.\
