	I dragged the mirror to the bathroom, fighting a slight tug that was pulling it back towards Lauren.  I have these cabinets beneath the sink that are a real bitch to open because of the way the wood\'92s swelled over time - takes two hands to get in there so I don\'92t even use the toothbrush rack inside anymore.  I give the doors a big yank and shove the mirror in there, then push them shut with my foot again.  I shut the bathroom door on the way out again just to make sure.  \
	Lauren\'92s sitting on the edge of the bed, looking all freaked out, and I guess it makes sense.  I put my arm around her and try to get her to lay down with me again, and she\'92s almost there when this knocking starts.  It keeps getting louder and louder until I hear those damn cabinet doors fling open and some stuff crashing.  I am super pissed right about now.  I get up and open the bathroom doors, and there\'92s a pair of eyes again, trying to navigate the little disc around the dark bathroom.  I don\'92t even stop it as it flies back out past me, I just go to the kitchen and open up my toolkit that I leave under that sink.  When I walk back into the bedroom the mirror is all up on Lauren, all this giggling coming from inside it.  I grab it with one hand and push it up against the wall, showing it what I\'92ve got in the other - a big old rusty hammer, claw end out.\
